1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:05,212
Okay, I had to lay off my entire social media team... of robots.

2
00:00:05,212 --> 00:00:12,750
Seriously, my AI agents were supposed to sound chill, but they came out sounding like a broken sleep meditation.

3
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:18,350
The visuals were even worse—pure 2015 Ken Burns slideshows.

4
00:00:18,350 --> 00:00:21,300
The root issue was they had no boss.

5
00:00:21,300 --> 00:00:23,525
So I fixed the code.

6
00:00:23,525 --> 00:00:27,275
I didn't add more features, I added governance.

7
00:00:27,275 --> 00:00:31,575
Now, the AI Creative Director has to approve everything.

8
00:00:31,575 --> 00:00:38,987
If a script sounds too hype-y or uses engagement bait like "smash that like button," it gets rejected instantly.

9
00:00:38,987 --> 00:00:44,275
Next up, we’re switching to moving text and linking up to real trend APIs.

10
00:00:44,275 --> 00:00:48,750
We’re not a content pipeline anymore; we’re a creative studio.

11
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:50,700
Learning as we go.

